    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"459227\">Violeta Hernández</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Minimal.2FIsLeast/near/531736630\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>How come <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Minimal#doc\">docs#Minimal</a> uses <code>α → Prop</code> while <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=IsLeast#doc\">docs#IsLeast</a> uses <code>Set α</code>?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>One answer is historical accident, but I think currently <code>Minimal</code> is used more for values which are minimal with respect to a predicate, whereas <code>IsLeast</code> is used more for sets.</p>",
